The retentiveness in me is forcing me to point out (sorry) that in EQ2, the tradeskilling system is completely different.  You level up just like any other class, but instead of getting XP for killing something, you get XP for crafting items.  You learn the recipes by purchasing the recipe books.  You gain the extra XP when you make your first pristine of each item (there are 4 qualities of the combines, from crude to pristine.)</div>
